# Next.js Development Rules

## App Router Guidelines
- Use the App Router for new projects
- Implement Server Components by default
- Use Client Components only when necessary (interactivity, hooks)
- Implement proper data fetching with `fetch` and caching strategies
- Use React Server Components for data fetching where possible
- Implement proper error handling with error.tsx files
- Use loading.tsx for loading states

## Performance Optimization
- Minimize 'use client' directives
- Implement proper image optimization with next/image
- Use dynamic imports for large components
- Implement proper code splitting
- Use Suspense boundaries effectively
- Implement incremental static regeneration for semi-static data
- Use edge functions for global performance

## Routing and Navigation
- Implement proper route grouping with folders
- Use layout.tsx for shared layouts
- Implement proper metadata for SEO
- Use Link component for client-side navigation
- Implement proper dynamic routes

## State Management
- Use React Context for global state when appropriate
- Consider Zustand for more complex state management
- Implement proper form handling with React Hook Form
- Use SWR or React Query for data fetching and caching

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Implement proper responsive design
- Use CSS variables for theming
- Consider CSS Modules for component-specific styling

## Accessibility
- Implement proper semantic HTML
- Use ARIA attributes when necessary
- Ensure keyboard navigation works properly
- Test with screen readers